<br>
Here's my feedback on the Plane of Hate discussion taking place there.<br>
<br>
We took our turn at bat tonight, Maestro knocked us into the dug out.  Fun fight, we'll be back at him soon -- a little wiser.<br>
<br>
Definately agree that while the zone should be kept on rotation for a short while longer, it really doesn't deserve to be there long term.  Hate is a much larger zone now.  When you kill the Mini-bosses's they're not down for a full day -- instead, mini's have placeholders on a 20-minute spawn, making this a zone that several guilds (or even strong groups) can camp -- all at the same time -- without futzing each other up.  Goofy old planes aggro is gone now, it's more like an indoor PoP zone now.<br>
<br>
I think SoE just turned this into another alternative for high-level XP groups.  Recommend that after the &quot;Gotta See the New Hate&quot; fervor dies down, Maestro and Inny go on rotation (perhaps), but the zone becomes open. <p><BR><img src=http://avengersinfaith.lfchosting.com/images/signatures/ShantarSig1.jpg height=189 width=408></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nyca>Nyca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Singing Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1698<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(6/7/03 10:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/slllyonec/EZemo/LeahHarp2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Posting privs on Guild Rep forum, and PoH feedback.</span><hr size=1> Done.<br>
