Which is why you need 40 planables to post. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The problem is that this was back when 40 was a number used to determine ability to succeed in a plane that could eat your corpse should you fail. <br>
<br>
The next statement you make...<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
I think the point is that the Plane of Hate is a pretty good exp zone for a group now.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
...proves that the situation has indeed changed quite a bit. I have been killing for epic drops in hate for a fair amount of time (not nearly as much as the enchanter I'm going up for) and the zone supports at least 2 fast pulling groups, and will likely, including the hard(er) mobs in the zone, support 3 to 5. That's a lot like the Guard/Crypt/Disco/Zoneout/Chef camp arrangement in Seb, and the mobs/xp/levelrange are nearly comparable, by and large. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
And refresh my memory but didn't everyone agree, that we probably should just leave it as is for the boss mobs.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'd have to disagree. There are no ring events, no script style kills (minus some funky things during the maestro fight, but that's restricted to the fight itself) so that reserving the plane to allow a guild to attempt a kill, is a herculean effort to ensure privacy... it would be similar, now, to asking people to leave seb while they kill trakanon. The xp areas, with perhaps the exception, maybe, of the maestro's stairs area, would not interfere in any way with raids. I would suggest that FCFS maestro/inny would be fine, until/unless someone asked for a rotational move. (Keep in mind that i'm not intersted in maestro at this time). <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
If you want to run an exp group, there are plenty of FFA days. We spent most of the weekend in Hate in an exp group working on an enchanter epic drop....we had company.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The enchanter drop, or any drop for that matter, is not impeded by having others in the zone. The only drawback to having another group in the area, is that *all* the spawns are not yours. Certainly, that is a drawback but not an unfair one, since the same thing occurs in every other zone in which items drop. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
However, if more than 3 separate exp groups come in it would not be worth it to be there for just exp. You would quickly be running over one another and mages and chanters and clerics would be cussing.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I disagree. If the groups were all sticking to only the 'easy' area then yes, it would be overcrowded, but in the same way that 2 groups can't (shouldn't) camp guard. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
So I think it should remain a reserve zone. So if your guild needs to go in and take out the boss or miniboss, they can do so without competeing with exp groups.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The mini bosses are on a random spawn with PH's, and the respawn is certainly less than half an hour. In 20 hours, I've seen perhaps 10 mini bosses in hate, not included in that number are the ones killed by other groups. If that is typical, it is a higher rate than named at the guard camp in seb. Killing mini's can be done with one group, not even a strong group. I personally kill with 3 other characters when I am in hate. <br>
<br>
Killing Maestro and Inny are raid forces, and if you take a raid force to kill Mini's in hate, well, you are probably too low to do the epic quests you are getting parts for. <br>
<br>
It will be, if an unreserved plane, a situation where groups compete with groups, as is the standard for the entire server, and raids FCFS on the maestro or inny or both, until/unless they decide to rotate them. It will not be a situation in which a single group blocks an entire raid from killing mobs. <br>
<br>
I would support removing hate from a 'reserved zone' and instead open it up to the use that it now is best suited for, after the initial time that we've waited to see if the zone is a raid, group, or mixed zone. I would offer that it is indeed a mixed zone, in a way very much analogous with Sebilis, by virtue of the 'boss' mobs and zone mobs being of quite a differant nature with regards to respawn, difficulty, and drop rates. <br>
<br>
