</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kathartic>Kathartic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>DHG - GL</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/13/03 2:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Posting privs on Guild Rep forum, and PoH feedback.</span><hr size=1> In case this thread is now a poll for guild rep input, I think leaving it on calendar is good idea.  It is not a typical experience zone though it can support more than one group it certainly doesn't support several disjointed groups or raids.<br>
<br>
Also, the content, even revised, is still geared for guilds/people in the same stage as it always was even though there is some more advanced mobs and loot available.  If DHG were just coming into the stage of doing old world planes I would like to have the same advantage all those who went before had in being able to actually schedule a raid for those epic pieces and gear and know that you will be able to do your raid.  Otherwise you struggle to get the numbers together to actually succeed then find that there are 2 groups there already and you now have your best raid force assembled and nothing to do.  There's not a lot of comparable raid zones not calendared.  I just remember when DHG was just getting to the old world planes and how much the calendar helped us because at the time it took all we had to do it.<br>
<br>
As it is on calendar there are a LOT of free days available.  We have, and I'm sure others have as well, shared the zone when it was &quot;ours&quot;.   However sharing with another group/guild is different than sharing with whoever might happen to be there which might be 2-3 groups.  <br>
<br>
As it is, no one is denied the ability to use the zone.  In fact the revamp has made it more accessible to shorter farming missions.  I've never heard someone say &quot;let's go to hate and get some exp&quot;.  We have discussed making single groups to farm so we can get better exp while doing it but not the same.  Having it on calendar does make it more accessible to guilds that are at the point of NEEDING that content as they can schedule the plane and since they might need a majority of their members to be successful can plan on it.  <br>
<br>
That's from my viewpoint anyway.  Maybe guilds that progressed like DHG don't really exist anymore /shrug  We did grow up much like the older guilds without benefit of recruiting already high level players with experience at these zones.  I was under the impression that many guilds/alliances grow up this way still in today's game.  Don't misunderstand me in that I acknowledge we had gear and knowledge that the earlier guilds didn't have on their first attempts.  I'm only pointing out that I believe there are guilds that still need that content for whom it is indeed a challenge for a raid.  And there maybe more guilds coming up in that fashion.<br>
<br>
I can see some room for argument on the &quot;qualifications for reservation&quot; though.  I'm not prepared to make that argument as I have no alternative solution in mind but it might make sense to relax the reservation qualifications some.   When we (as the GotR alliance at the time) first got our 40 planables for reservation we struggled hard with that place and it wasn't really fun at first.  So maybe it isn't an unreasonable number.<br>
<br>
DHG votes for leaving on reservation and seperate rotations for Inny and Maestro if guilds killing them feel the need for rotation.  Seems like same caveat with Fear and CT would be appropriate in that it be done in coordination with the reserving guild if it's reserved that day.  I could also see fit for a modification the guidelines for that plane.  Waiting until a reserving guild has left is really not needed due to respawn rate.  It would seem more appropriate that when the reserving guild arrive any existing people should be prepared to leave if an arrangement for coexistance can't be made.   Attempting to make arrangements with the reserving guild in advance would seem preferable but there is really nothing lost to the reserving guild by someone being in plane ahead of them.<br>
<br>
And to add on last minute thought... the calendar actually facilitates everyone in use of the zone.  Not only do reserving guilds know they have a place to go, those planning to go know when is not a good time to plan and/or who to talk to if they want to arrange a share.  Last two times we've been up there we shared with others.  Indeed one time we went on a FCFS day and the 3 box that was there allowed us to have a piece for ours.  It seemed a much more amiable situation for all parties.  Not once did someone have to say &quot;you took one of our mobs&quot;.  Never did a tracker show up and grab the mini-boss that finally spawned after we killed it's ph 17 times.  <br>
<br>
Kathartic <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roggulbuk>Roggulbuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><marquee>Newbie Admin!</marquee> <BR>
Watch him break stuff!</span><br>  Posts: 1620<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/13/03 2:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Posting privs on Guild Rep forum, and PoH feedback.</span><hr size=1> The problem is not so much that the plane can be, or should be reserved, but the consequences for going in 'on someone else's turn'. <br>
<br>
When it was in it's original form, mini's spawned on a much longer span than they do now. Hate had a long, long repop and once mobs were down, with the exception of the wandering patrols, that was that. <br>
<br>
Now, the repop is quick, and the mini's much more frequent. <br>
<br>
Additionally, any guild that struggles to put together a mini's raid in hate, hasn't looked at the actual statistics of the mobs themselves. Top hit of 500, minor casting, and well under 15k hp, probably closer to 10, make for a mob that is the wimpy little brother of some mobs in the king camp in sebilis. The pulls are single, not the mass trains of the old days. <br>
<br>
I really don't mind if a guild wants to reserve a day, or what not. The problem comes when the guild that reserves a day pops up and finds someone else there. <br>
<br>
See, the reason for the reservation in the past is that it was a long spawn, that was difficult to coordinate around and dangerous in most respects due to the type of zone in area (IE: aggro immediately from several mobs, some very hard to mez).<br>
<br>
Now, I could zone a naked level 46 bard into hate, and tell jokes at the nearest mobs if I was inclined. The repops are as close to instant as they could be when you're dealing with epic drops and the like. <br>
<br>
The point is, that I'm driving at, that since there is no consequence for a group being there, and having killed mobs that will repop in 20 minutes, and have many, many other mobs up and about, there should not be a punishment for being there, as there would be if a guild dropped in and found 3 groups already clearing fear and taking the drops there. <br>
<br>
The nature of the new hate is such that attempting to reserve the entire zone is at the same time, both unnecessary and greedy. The same types and kinds of mobs will pop, just as fast as you can kill them, if not nearly as fast as you can kill them, and if you are able to bring 4 groups up, and the area would support 5, is it really justifiable to punish the 1st group already there, for being in a zone that is basically now the same as any other xp zone?<br>
<br>
Those people that do not go to hate for xp are missing what would likely be a good challenge and good xp for the 51-59 range, and there are areas that provide passable AA xp at levels 61 and up, though the xp drops off sharply. <br>
<br>
From the normal, average zone mobs, there is really no loot that would be worth the time of any group in the zone. The old hate armor drops are substandard to many, if not all, kunark armor items for the same class, and drop with an almost equal frequency. <br>
<br>
The mobs that would be desireable for loot, are of a completely differant nature. Any guild that has *any* trouble fielding any 3 people who couldn't together kill a hate mini boss, will likely fail horribly against the maestro. Yes, I would say that even 3 warriors with proper aggro management from a guild that could kill maestro would own the hate mini's into the ground. <br>
<br>
The issue of reserving the zone is, now, to me, a moot one, since any and all mobs that are in the zone will replace within 30 minutes; if I am there and you have reserved the plane, than I would certainly leave if asked. However, I think that due to the nature of the mobs and the length of their repop, that only the most arrogant and hostile human beings would seek retribution for that 'transgression'. <br>
<br>
It would be similar to guard getting mad at the crypt group that moved in half an hour ago because they killed the mobs on the way down. The mobs are already replaced by repop at that time, and I seriously doubt if the intentions of the calendar resevations of hate were to allow a zone full of fast repopping mobs to be reserved on the peril of being somehow punished by the conventions of the RTA.<br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
