Watch him break stuff!</span><br>  Posts: 1628<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/13/03 10:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Posting privs on Guild Rep forum, and PoH feedback.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Now, why would you want those other 4 guilds/entities to have to argue with a few/many groups to get what they thought they were going to get?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I don't want them to have to argue. Zoning in and seeing a group or two there and saying &quot;hey guys, our booking day&quot; isn't arguing. If the groups don't leave, there is as much (or little) that can be done about it now, as could be done about it a year ago. <br>
<br>
I'm not asking for free reign to kill the maestro, or whatever else. I'm suggesting that it is unreasonable to deny access to an entire zone for 24 hours, for the sake of one group's 4 hour raid. I mean, there is a hugely, hugely strong case to take it completely off the calandar, (easy zone, fast repops, mobs that drop epic parts are easy to get, loot mobs are rotation style in-zone, etc, and the argument that epic drops are protected by the calandar day is defeated by the fact that we don't reserve 24 hour periods in the City of Mist, yet it has epic drops for ranger, mage, shadowknight and shaman, at least). If the worry about booking a day to safely AE it all is valid, than we should be reserving CoM as well, for whatever reason. I'm not suggesting it's removed from the rotation. I just think that we should allow groups to go up, and take the regular zone mobs when they are otherwise not being contested in any way. We're not talking about ganking the only mob they wanted to kill, we're talking about not removing the reservation rights from an entity who kills 30 minute repop mobs before the guild that has reserved the plane is starting their raid. <br>
<br>
The zone itself is not unlike any other unprotected-by-calandar zone that has epic drops off fast respawning mobs, and I'm just wondering why, really, the reasoning seems to be &quot;It doesn't happen a lot that people want to go on a day that is booked&quot; and &quot;Some people need large groups to kill there&quot;. There's no, seemingly, argument that having groups in there killing zone trash would be a problem, minor or major, for the reserving guild's persuit of epic drops, provided the non-reserving group leaves when asked. <br>
<br>
I mean, if we reserve a day and go up for 5 minutes for our &quot;raid&quot;, does that mean people have to stay out for the 24 hours that we have it reserved for? If we are raiding at 11pm PST, why would people have to wait all day and most of the EST night and not be able to go in for the mobs that respawn quickly?<br>
<br>
I just really can't see a 'harm' and as such, in the 'no harm, no foul' way of life that we have around here, it doesn't gel. <br>
<br>
Like, Hate is booked tonight, right now. At 11pm EST, if I see that hate is empty, I have no way to know if the zone has not yet been used, or has already been used by whatever guild has it booked. After the reserving guild leaves, it's FFA, obviously. If I go up and kill stuff before the start of the PST Guild's raid start, but the dead mobs refresh in 20 minutes, is that really worth being against the rules?<br>
<br>
I'm big on following written rules. I don't intend to willingly or knowingly be in hate before a raiding guild has used it for the day. But it's very, very, very silly to treat hate like it is some vaunted and magical place that requires a full day to ensure repops and preparation time. Believe me, I've not at all forgotten the preparation for the old hate my guild used to do. Even the last time we went up, long after ToV HoT armor and gear, we went in hard and took nothing for granted in that zone. <br>
<br>
The new hate, is a playground. Not because of my gear or level, but because of the layout, frequency of mobs, their proximity to other mobs, and their capacity for chain aggro being greatly reduced. Their social aggro ranges are very small as well. <br>
<br>
All I'm suggesting, is that if there is no harm, there should be no foul. If I kill mobs in hate that will repop in 20 minutes, and a guild asks me to leave, and I leave without issue on their reserved day, I want it recognized and understood that it is a 'no harm' situation, because that is in fact what it is. I'm not suggesting I'm going to kill maestro and hand and inny, and deny their raid content. I'm not keeping them from getting anything, and I'm not disrupting their raid for longer than it takes to say /ooc we're here now, we've got the plane booked, we'd appreciate the plane to ourselves. The only delay I would ever give to that ooc, would be &quot;Right away, have one mob up and then we're gone, good luck&quot;.<br>
<br>
I don't think that anyone, considering the facts of the new zone, the types of mobs in it, or any of the situational issues that may arise, would find that a 'harmful' situation. <br>
<br>
My bottom line, really, is that it doesn't make sense to not allow yard trash to be killed in hate, for the reason that it is the way we've always done it. The zone is not the same, the rules should reflect that. Respect dictates, and rightly, that if the zone reservation system is wanted by even a minority, that we keep it, and respect dictates that if someone who has reserved the plane wants it, they get it when they arrive, no problem. But respect doesn't, in my view, go so far as to leave the entire zone empty for even half the day, when it is litterally zero harm to the guild going up, if you kill the mobs that will have respawned by the time they get there, or will respawn at the absolute longest. It is beyond the scope of the original rules, it is beyond the scope of guilds asking for respect. <br>
<br>
Believe me, I respect other people's raids, groups, camps, loot, effort, toons, and game enjoyment. I won't engage in behavior that makes the game 'worse' for someone else. This behavior doesn't make the game worse for anyone, in any factual or logical way. <br>
<br>
Anyway, that's me, if it is still so obviously a horrible idea, I'll let it rest, but I just don't see the reason for the opposition to it; the drop frequency won't change, the available mobs won't change, the possibility for a hampered raid is virtually non existant, the zone is no longer unique in that it has long, long repops on basic zone mobs, it's no differant than many other unreserved zones, the only direction I can see the opposition coming from is the 'it's the way it is' and I don't agree with or understand the reluctance. <br>
<br>
*shrug*<br>
<br>
Yers, <p><font color="blue">Roggulbuk Bonesmasher</font><br>
<b><i><font color="Orange">Warlord of Clan Bashemded</font></i></b><br><font color="black">An Cat Dubh</font><br>Me Mudders Yungust Son<br>Less babies, mor fibur!!<br>
