 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roggulbuk>Roggulbuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><marquee>Newbie Admin!</marquee> <BR>
Watch him break stuff!</span><br>  Posts: 1631<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(8/14/03 1:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=388.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Posting privs on Guild Rep forum, and PoH feedback.</span><hr size=1> Strange that I wasn't complete in an answer... *grin* sorry about that. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Why the insistance that someone HAS to go up on a Reserved Day? Why only those days? The other 24 aren't any good? Are there really that many people that want to go there? Are they standing in line, champing at the bit, cursing and moaning cause they can't get in RIGHT NOW?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm not suggesting that people &quot;have&quot; to go on any day in particular. When they do go up on reserved days, because they're not harming anything, why would they be punished? Or rather, why would it be against 'the rules'?<br>
<br>
Why do people want to/have to log in? The measure of if someone wants to go, is just that: if they want to go. They don't *have* to do it, any more than a guild *has* to book a day, really. They could also just use one of those FFA days if they wanted to. The point isn't that a person wanting to go to hate wants to go on a reserved day, or that they have to go on a reserved day. The point is that going on any day, reserved or not, and killing mobs that respawn in 30 minutes, isn't doing a single drop of harm to anyone. As long as people are not impeding someone's raid, harming their group, or any other use on a reserved or unreserved day, I can't see the justification for it being against the rules. <br>
<br>
We have rules to protect people, and groups. That's what they do. They protect them from having a raid ruined by not having mobs. They protect them from having the chance at an item lost, because of the mobs having been killed already.<br>
<br>
What protection is granted in this case? No one would be worried about their mob being up in hate, since all but Inny, Maestro and (maybe) hand are on 30 minute respawns. If people are after those specific mobs, and desire them, the rotation system is much more suited to protecting them. Even with that said, the desire to be able to kill zone mobs does not equate to someone losing their chance at Inny or Maestro or A hand of the Maestro by a rogue guild on a reserved day. I am fully in favor of whatever consequences are deemed appropriate for anyone killing a mob that does not respawn in under an hour in a reserved zone. That would significantly hamper a raid there, especially if that mob was their only target (if you will allow me the logical conclusion, that any guild going to attempt maestro or Innoruk right now, likely won't want any of the loot that drops off the regular zone mobs, and any guild that wants the loot drops off the regular zone mobs and has to raid to get them, won't be killing maestro or inny any time soon...) And to that end, while I think it is unlikely that the 'stolen' raid mobs would occur on the reservation day itself, I am willing to cede the possibility that it could happen, and any persons in hate, in my mind, who are on someone else's reserve day, are very wrong to take any mob that will not be back in 30 minutes.<br>
<br>
Look, maybe if I approach the situation this way...<br>
<br>
If I, and 5 members of my guild, are killing zone mobs and a guild comes in and says &quot;Guys, we reserved the plane for today&quot; and we say &quot;Right you are, we're on our way out, have a good hunt&quot; and leave, what are the consequences, and do you think those consequences as prescribed by the RTA now, are fair, and fit the transgression as we see it?<br>
<br>
The conditions of the zone when my group leaves, is that there are no mobs dead that will not repop within 30 minutes, and that no raid mobs have been killed, at all. <br>
<br>
Yers, <p><font color="blue">Roggulbuk Bonesmasher</font><br>
